data.enText: to give a lot of your time and effort to a particular activity or purpose because you think it is important
She dedicates herself to her work.

data.chText: 他毕生致力于帮助穷人。
data.enText: He dedicated his life to helping the poor.

data.chText: （在书、音乐或作品的前部）题献词
data.enText: to say at the beginning of a book, a piece of music or a performance that you are doing it for sb, as a way of thanking them or showing respect

data.chText: 谨以此书献给我的父母。
data.enText: This book is dedicated to my parents.

data.chText: 为…举行奉献典礼；为（建筑物等）举行落成典礼
data.enText: to hold an official ceremony to say that a building or an object has a special purpose or is special to the memory of a particular person

data.chText: 这座小教堂于1880年举行献堂典礼。
为阵亡将士纪念碑举行了落成典礼。
data.enText: A memorial stone was dedicated to those who were killed in the war.

means: (在书、音乐或作品的前部)题献词
为(建筑物等)举行落成典礼

ex.chText: 他毕生致力于为人民服务。
ex.enText: He dedicated his life to serving the people.

synonyms.bx: 较正式用词，通常指献身于崇高的事业或活动。

ex.enText: The priest consecrated himself to the Church.

synonyms.bx: 尤指为宗教而奉献、献身。

ex.enText: She devoted her attention to her work.

ex.chText: 他投身于发展航天工业。
ex.enText: He devoted himself to developing the space industry.

synonyms.bx: 指把生命、精力、时间等用于某一目标、事业等，常与介词 to 连用。

tr: set apart to sacred uses with solemn rites, of a church
inscribe or address by way of compliment
example: She dedicated her book to her parents

tr: give entirely to a specific person, activity, or cause
example: She committed herself to the work of God
give one's talents to a good cause
consecrate your life to the church

tr: open to public use, as of a highway, park, or building
example: The Beauty Queen spends her time dedicating parks and nursing homes

value.def: If you say that someone has dedicated themselves to something, you approve of the fact that they have decided to give a lot of time and effort to it because they think that it is important.

example.ex: Back on the island, he dedicated himself to politics...
example.tran: 回到岛上后，他便投身于政治。

example.ex: Bessie has dedicated her life to caring for others.
example.tran: 贝茜一生都致力于照顾他人。

example.ex: He's quite dedicated to his students.
example.tran: 他一门心思都扑在学生身上。

example.ex: ...a company staffed by capable and dedicated people.
example.tran: 拥有一支能干、敬业的员工队伍的公司

example.ex: We admire her dedication to the cause of humanity...
example.tran: 我们敬佩她对人类事业的献身精神。

example.ex: To be successful takes hard work and dedication.
example.tran: 成功需要付出艰苦的努力，需要有全身心投入的精神。

value.def: If someone dedicates something such as a book, play, or piece of music to you, they mention your name, for example in the front of a book or when a piece of music is performed, as a way of showing affection or respect for you.

example.ex: She dedicated her first album to Woody Allen...
example.tran: 她把自己的第一张专辑献给了伍迪·艾伦。

example.ex: This book is dedicated to the memory of my mother.
example.tran: 谨以此书献给我已故的母亲。

value.tran: 把(书、戏剧、音乐作品等)献（给）

value.def: If a building or church is dedicated to someone, a formal ceremony is held to show that the building will always be associated with them.

example.ex: The other day, in a little church near Brighton, a window was dedicated to the memory of the Revd. Michael Scott...
example.tran: 几天前，在布赖顿附近的一个小教堂，人们以一扇窗户来纪念迈克尔·斯科特牧师。

example.ex: The church is dedicated to St Mary of Bec.
example.tran: 该教堂供奉的是贝克的圣玛丽。

value.tran: 为(建筑物或教堂)举行奉献（或落成）典礼

example.tran: 大屠杀纪念馆的落成典礼

example.ex: Some 250 guests attended the dedication ceremony.
example.tran: 约有 250 位来宾参加了奉献典礼。
